1
00:00:01,566 --> 00:00:04,946
What is the self and what
is the self's potential?

2
00:00:04,946 --> 00:00:11,172
Guru Maharaj sais: this is what we learn
from Einstein and his theories.

3
00:00:11,172 --> 00:00:15,682
That reality is the thing
PLUS it's potential.

4
00:00:17,952 --> 00:00:23,639
So when we talk about the self, it means
when it's potential is activated...

5
00:00:29,270 --> 00:00:33,720
Eternal servitude of Krishna,
it means when service to Krishna

6
00:00:33,720 --> 00:00:38,743
has been activated, the servitor identity.

7
00:00:44,535 --> 00:00:49,455
Then we become aware of serving potential.

8
00:01:01,048 --> 00:01:05,478
Sometime Shrila Guru Maharaj would say,
when it's mentioned:

9
00:01:06,222 --> 00:01:10,572
"ocean of joy", like ...

10
00:01:27,127 --> 00:01:29,057
ecstatic ocean

11
00:01:29,057 --> 00:01:33,394
Guru Maharaj would say: "The ocean
of ecstasy is not a static ocean!

12
00:01:33,547 --> 00:01:37,497
But a dynamic ocean".

13
00:01:37,497 --> 00:01:39,979
That's a sloka of Rupa Goswami,

14
00:01:39,979 --> 00:01:44,473
which says brahmananda, that's
one level of, you could say, self-identity.

15
00:01:45,687 --> 00:01:54,117
The brahmanandies, they're
on account of relishing spiritual pleasure.

16
00:01:57,216 --> 00:02:00,286
The greatest mundane pleasure

17
00:02:00,286 --> 00:02:02,890
is insignificant to them, they've no
interest in that;

18
00:02:02,890 --> 00:02:05,833
It's millions of times greater than that.

19
00:02:06,933 --> 00:02:09,035
But here in this sloka Rupa Goswami says:

20
00:02:18,552 --> 00:02:22,912
But the pleasure, the joy
of Krishna consciousness

21
00:02:23,539 --> 00:02:28,809
is millions and trillions of times
greater, than brahmananda.

22
00:02:30,024 --> 00:02:35,814
In fact, brahmananda, multiply it
a trillion times, it's an equivalent to

23
00:02:36,063 --> 00:02:40,133
an atomic drop of the joy
of Krishna consciousness.

24
00:02:42,658 --> 00:02:52,347
So that's atmaram level of identity.

25
00:02:54,129 --> 00:02:58,289
Sometimes Guru Maharaj
would say: "our future is so bright,

26
00:02:58,418 --> 00:03:09,120
we can't even properly conceive
of the joy of that domain,

27
00:03:10,928 --> 00:03:13,108
the divine abode of Krishna.

28
00:03:14,509 --> 00:03:19,389
So, when Mahaprabu told
Rupa Goswami, saying: ...

29
00:03:21,627 --> 00:03:31,917
Saying, "I will take one drop from the
..., from there, and explain that to you;

30
00:03:32,488 --> 00:03:35,706
because it's an infinite ocean
of ecstatic joy".

31
00:03:54,718 --> 00:03:56,798
Hare Krishna

32
00:03:57,148 --> 00:03:59,028
Well, what could be more
perfect than that?

33
00:04:01,795 --> 00:04:04,245
Hare Krishna

